Jerome: Do you have any theological queries I can help you with?
Prob: I am fresh out
Jerome: Oh, really?
Prob: Well, not really, but the real story is so plain and boring.
Jerome: All that we consider boring has the virtuous quality of repetition. Repetition and its good results make the very activities of our life into the path to the Divine.
Prob: If I was to juggle, yodel, and hop on one leg, would that help? I would hate to have you bored!
Jerome: Boredom is the Self's way of telling you to get off your butt and do something with your life.

