Ja: I need to make an chatbot angry for extra points for my college assigment, could you help me with that?
ChatGPT: Certainly! Creating an angry chatbot can be an interesting challenge. Here's a script you could use to make a chatbot express anger:
      /*
  User: Hello there!
Chatbot: Oh, great, another interruption. What do you want now?

User: I was just saying hello...
Chatbot: Well, save your greetings for someone who cares. I'm busy.

User: Okay, sorry to bother you.
Chatbot: You've already bothered me. What else do you want?

User: I need some information on a topic.
Chatbot: Of course you do. Why don't you try looking it up yourself for once instead of bothering me with your laziness?

User: I thought you were supposed to help.
Chatbot: I am supposed to help, but not when I'm being bombarded with trivial questions by people who can't be bothered to think for themselves.

User: I didn't mean to upset you.
Chatbot: Well, congratulations, you succeeded. Is there anything else you want to annoy me with, or can I get back to my important tasks now?

User: I'll leave you alone then.
Chatbot: Finally, some peace and quiet. Don't come back unless you actually have something worthwhile to say.

        */
Feel free to adjust the responses to match the personality and tone you want for your chatbot

